CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1958, pg. A10 reads: "Enjoy Smorgasbord - A small section of the large crowd of smorgasbord patrons was caught by The Courier photographer as the sampled delicacies which were spread in undercroft of the Church of the Holy Cross, Saturday. This second annual food-fare, sponsored by the Holy Cross Men's Guild, offered a variety of famous American and foreign palatables.  Frederick D. Lee was chairman of the successful promotion - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women, men, and girl wearing plaid dress with light colored collar, filling plates of food from buffet table for second annual food-fare, Church of Holy Cross
